<div class="mb-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-4">
  <div>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">NodeDB on Rails</h1>
    <div class="text-muted-foreground">
      End-to-end demo of the
      <a href="https://github.com/mkhairi/activerecord-nodedb-adapter">activerecord-nodedb-adapter</a>
      stack — Rails 8 → ActiveRecord → NodeDB, over pgwire or the
      native binary protocol.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="flex gap-2">
    <% if @daemon_up %>
      <span class="badge text-green-600" data-variant="outline"><i class="ti ti-circle-check mr-1"></i>daemon connected</span>
    <% else %>
      <span class="badge text-red-600" data-variant="outline"><i class="ti ti-plug-off mr-1"></i>daemon unreachable</span>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="alert mt-4" role="alert">
  <i class="ti ti-alert-triangle"></i>
  <h2>Alpha demo — disposable data only.</h2>
  <section>
    Every layer here is experimental: the gems have never run in
    production, and NodeDB's current upstream loses document-collection
    contents across daemon restarts. Wipe + reseed after restarts; see
    <%= link_to "Docs → Operating notes", docs_path(anchor: "operating-notes") %>.
  </section>
</div>

<div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
  <% [
    ["Articles",          articles_path,     "ti-files",           "document_strict CRUD — plain ActiveRecord over a strict document collection"],
    ["Posts (FTS)",       posts_path,        "ti-search",          "full-text search with CREATE FULLTEXT INDEX, ranked + fuzzy queries"],
    ["Locations & Map",   locations_path,    "ti-map-pin",         "spatial writes via geometry constructors, haversine radius reads"],
    ["Social Graph",      social_nodes_path, "ti-affiliate",       "graph edges, traversal, PageRank over the edge store"],
    ["Timeseries",        metrics_path,      "ti-chart-line",      "TIME_KEY collections, time_bucket aggregates, realtime system-gauge charts"],
    ["Vector search",     embeddings_path,   "ti-vector-triangle", "SEARCH ... USING VECTOR nearest-neighbour with projected distance"],
    ["KV Store",          kv_sessions_path,  "ti-key",             "key-value engine with TTLs — set / get / exists / delete"],
    ["Audit (bitemporal)", audit_logs_path,  "ti-clock-hour-3",    "every committed version retained; AS OF SYSTEM TIME time travel"],
    ["Tenants",           tenants_path,      "ti-building-community", "server-side isolation: tenant-bound users, per-connection scoping"],
    ["Server info",       server_info_path,  "ti-server",          "connection, migrations, collections, operational SHOW commands"]
  ].each do |label, path, icon, blurb| %>
    <%= link_to path, class: "card h-full transition-colors hover:bg-muted/50" do %>
      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-1 font-semibold"><i class="ti <%= icon %> mr-2 text-primary"></i><%= label %></h2>
        <div class="text-muted-foreground text-sm"><%= blurb %></div>
      </section>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
</div>

<div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
  <div class="card h-full">
    <header><h2>Stack</h2></header>
    <section>
      <dl class="grid gap-x-8 gap-y-2 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <dt class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">rails</dt>
        <dd class="font-medium"><code><%= @gem_versions["rails"] || Rails.version %></code></dd>
        <dt class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">activerecord-nodedb-adapter</dt>
        <dd class="font-medium"><code><%= @gem_versions["activerecord-nodedb-adapter"] || "(not loaded)" %></code></dd>
        <dt class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">nodedb-ruby</dt>
        <dd class="font-medium"><code><%= @gem_versions["nodedb-ruby"] || "(not loaded)" %></code></dd>
        <dt class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">pg (libpq)</dt>
        <dd class="font-medium"><code><%= @gem_versions["pg"] || "(not loaded)" %></code></dd>
        <dt class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">transports</dt>
        <dd class="font-medium"><code>pgwire :6432</code> · <code>native :6433</code></dd>
      </dl>
    </section>
  </div>
  <div class="card h-full">
    <header><h2>Start here</h2></header>
    <section>
      <ol class="mb-2 list-decimal space-y-1 pl-5">
        <li><%= link_to "Docs", docs_path %> — how each engine demo works, with the migration + model code behind it.</li>
        <li><%= link_to "Server info", server_info_path %> — live connection, collections, and ops counters.</li>
        <li>Pick an engine card above and poke it — every page writes and reads a real NodeDB collection.</li>
      </ol>
      <div class="text-muted-foreground text-sm">
        Full test pass: <code>rake test:both_transports</code> +
        <code>scripts/feature_smoke.rb</code> over pgwire AND native.
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</div>
